# Quick Mental Rules

### Register Size → Python Size

```text
al  -> 1 byte  -> bytes([x])

ax  -> 2 bytes -> to_bytes(2,"little")

eax -> 4 bytes -> to_bytes(4,"little")

rax -> 8 bytes -> to_bytes(8,"little")
```

### Reversing Rule

```text
Read size from register.
Decode using that size.
Place bytes at the correct offset.
Reconstruct memory.
```

### Never Do

```text
Use comparison order.
```

### Always Do

```text
Use memory offsets.
```
